      • getUseSystemDate

        public java.lang.Boolean getUseSystemDate()
        If this is true (the default) then these fields will be populated with the current system date: ADDED_DATE (on inserts) UPDATED_DATE (on inserts and updates) If false, the value of the fields as populated will be used. Fields annotated with @CurrentDateField will always be populated with the system date
        Returns:

      • setUseSystemDate

        public void setUseSystemDate​(java.lang.Boolean useSystemDate)
        If this is true (the default) then these fields will be populated with the current system date: ADDED_DATE (on inserts) UPDATED_DATE (on inserts and updates) If false, the value of the fields as populated will be used. Fields annotated with @CurrentDateField will always be populated with the system date
